verses.text_plain: Paul, a prisoner for Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, To Philemon our beloved fellow worker
verses.verse_html:
1Paul, aa prisoner for Christ Jesus, and bTimothy our brother,

To Philemon our beloved fellow worker

verses.text_plain: and Apphia our sister and Archippus our fellow soldier, and the church in your house:
verses.verse_html: 2and Apphia our sister and cArchippus our dfellow soldier, and ethe church in your house:

verses.text_plain: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
verses.verse_html: 3 fGrace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.

verses.text_plain: I thank my God always when I remember you in my prayers,
verses.verse_html: 4 gI thank my God always when I remember you in my prayers,

verses.text_plain: because I hear of your love and of the faith that you have toward the Lord Jesus and for all the saints,
verses.verse_html: 5because I hhear of your love and iof the faith that you have toward the Lord Jesus and for all the saints,

verses.text_plain: and I pray that the sharing of your faith may become effective for the full knowledge of every good thing that is in us for the sake of Christ.
verses.verse_html:
6and I pray that the sharing of your faith may become effective for the full jknowledge of every good thing that is in us for the sake of Christ.
Or for Christs service

verses.text_plain: For I have derived much joy and comfort from your love, my brother, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you.
verses.verse_html: 7For I have derived much joy and lcomfort from your love, my brother, because the hearts of the saints mhave been refreshed through you.

verses.text_plain: Accordingly, though I am bold enough in Christ to command you to do what is required,
verses.verse_html: 8Accordingly, nthough I am bold enough in Christ to command you to do owhat is required,

verses.text_plain: yet for loves sake I prefer to appeal to you  I, Paul, an old man and now a prisoner also for Christ Jesus
verses.verse_html: 9yet for loves sake I prefer to appeal to youI, Paul, an old man and now pa prisoner also for Christ Jesus

verses.text_plain: I appeal to you for my child, Onesimus, whose father I became in my imprisonment.
verses.verse_html:
10I appeal to you for qmy child, rOnesimus,
 Onesimus means useful (see verse 11) or beneficial (see verse 20)
 twhose father I became in my imprisonment.

footnotes.body_text: Onesimus means useful (see verse 11) or beneficial (see verse 20)
footnotes.body_html: Onesimus means useful (see verse 11) or beneficial (see verse 20)

verses.text_plain: (Formerly he was useless to you, but now he is indeed useful to you and to me.)
verses.verse_html: 11(Formerly he was useless to you, but now he is indeed useful to you and to me.)

verses.text_plain: I am sending him back to you, sending my very heart.
verses.verse_html: 12I am sending him back to you, sending my very heart.

verses.text_plain: I would have been glad to keep him with me, in order that he might serve me on your behalf during my imprisonment for the gospel,
verses.verse_html: 13I would have been glad to keep him with me, in order that he might serve me uon your behalf vduring my imprisonment for the gospel,

verses.text_plain: but I preferred to do nothing without your consent in order that your goodness might not be by compulsion but of your own accord.
verses.verse_html: 14but I preferred to do nothing without your consent in order that your goodness might not be wby compulsion but of your own accord.

verses.text_plain: For this perhaps is why he was parted from you for a while, that you might have him back forever,
verses.verse_html: 15For this perhaps is why xhe was parted from you for a while, that you might have him back forever,

verses.text_plain: no longer as a bondservant but more than a bondservant, as a beloved brother  especially to me, but how much more to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
16 yno longer as a bondservant
Or slave; twice in this verse (for the contextual rendering of the Greek word doulos, see Preface)
 but more than a bondservant, as aaa beloved brotherespecially to me, but how much more to you, abboth in the flesh and in the Lord.

verses.text_plain: So if you consider me your partner, receive him as you would receive me.
verses.verse_html: 17So if you consider me acyour partner, receive him as you would receive me.

verses.text_plain: If he has wronged you at all, or owes you anything, charge that to my account.
verses.verse_html: 18If he has wronged you at all, or owes you anything, charge that to my account.

verses.text_plain: I, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will repay itto say nothing of your owing me even your own self.
verses.verse_html: 19 adI, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will repay itto say nothing of your owing me even your own self.

verses.text_plain: Yes, brother, I want some benefit from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in Christ.
verses.verse_html: 20Yes, brother, I want some benefit from you in the Lord. aeRefresh my heart in Christ.

verses.text_plain: Confident of your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even more than I say.
verses.verse_html: 21 afConfident of your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even more than I say.

verses.text_plain: At the same time, prepare a guest room for me, for I am hoping that through your prayers I will be graciously given to you.
verses.verse_html: 22At the same time, prepare a guest room for me, for agI am hoping that ahthrough your prayers aiI will be graciously given to you.

verses.text_plain: Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends greetings to you,
verses.verse_html: 23 ajEpaphras, my akfellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends greetings to you,

verses.text_plain: and so do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers.
verses.verse_html: 24and so do alMark, amAristarchus, anDemas, and aoLuke, my fellow workers.

verses.text_plain: The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
verses.verse_html: 25 apThe grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
